        cons: ['The logos rely heavily on a massive underlying database of standard fonts and stock vector icons; it cannot create a completely hand-drawn, highly unique, bespoke artistic logo (like a human illustrator could)', 'Highly experienced designers will spot an AI-generated Looka logo immediately due to structural layout similarities', 'The editor, while easy to use, lacks the absolute pixel-perfect manipulation capabilities of true vector software like Illustrator', 'There is no free download option; while generating designs is free, obtaining the actual files requires purchase'],
        pricing_overview: `<p>Looka allows users to generate and edit logos infinitely for free. Pricing triggers upon download. They offer a one-time purchase option (Basic or Premium Logo Package) for downloading just the logo files. However, they aggressively push the Brand Kit Subscription, an annual SaaS fee that provides the logo files plus continuous, unlimited access to the hundreds of automatically generated marketing and social media templates.</p>`,
        comparison_summary: `<p>Looka competes against Tailor Brands, Canva, and professional marketplaces like Fiverr. Canva is incredible for ongoing graphic design but lacks a dedicated, intelligent brand-generation workflow. Fiverr provides cheap human designers, but quality is a massive gamble, and revisions take days. Tailor Brands is highly similar but pushes heavily into LLC formation. Looka differentiates itself by heavily emphasizing the aesthetic quality and breadth of its *Brand Kit*. It is the best choice for a founder who wants to instantly look like a million-dollar company on day one, acquiring all the assets they need without gambling on a cheap freelancer.</p>`
